
================================================================================
  FINAL EXPANSION: REMAINING v1 SCREEN SPECIFICATIONS
================================================================================
  Phase 1: A1, B1, D1, D3, E2, F3
  Phase 3: J1, J2, J3, J4
  Phase v2 (deferred): K1, K2, K3
  Total: 13 screens completing the full 42+13=55 screen coverage
================================================================================


SCREEN A1: SPLASH SCREEN (Free — all tiers)
Phase: 1
─────────────────────────────────────────

  PURPOSE:
    App launch screen. The "curse-breaking" brand reveal animation.
    Covers app initialization time (~1.5s). Checks auth state, routes to
    Onboarding (first launch) or Home (returning user). Sets the brand
    tone from the very first millisecond.

  FRONTEND (Flutter):
    Package: feature_onboarding
    Route: / (initial route)
    Key Widgets:
      - SplashAnimation — Rive animation: purple glow → gold flash → logo solidifies
        Duration: 1.5s total (800ms glow, 400ms flash, 300ms settle)
      - SplashBackground — midnight purple gradient (#0F0A1A → #1A0533)
      - LogoReveal — UNJYNX wordmark fades in after animation (200ms fadeIn)
    State Management:
      - splashProvider (FutureProvider) — checks auth state via Logto SDK
        Result: AuthState.authenticated | AuthState.unauthenticated | AuthState.firstLaunch
      - initializationProvider — preloads user preferences, Drift DB, notification state
    Packages (pub.dev):
      - rive ^0.13.0 — brand animation (or lottie ^3.0.0 if using Lottie file)
      - shared_preferences ^2.3.0 — first-launch detection (isFirstLaunch flag)
    Drift Tables (local):
      - (none — splash reads from SharedPreferences only)
    GoRouter:
      - redirect logic:
        firstLaunch=true → /onboarding/welcome (B1)
        authenticated=true → /home (C1)
        authenticated=false → /auth/login (A2)

  BACKEND (Hono/TypeScript):
    Endpoints:
      (none — splash is fully client-side)

    Business Logic:
      - No server call on splash. Auth token validation happens lazily after routing.
      - If stored auth token exists, validate on first API call (not on splash).
      - This ensures instant startup even without internet (offline-first).

  DATA FLOW:
    App launch → SplashAnimation plays → splashProvider checks SharedPreferences
    (isFirstLaunch) → if first launch: route to B1 → if returning: check Logto
    auth token in secure storage → valid: route to C1, invalid: route to A2

  INTERACTIONS & ANIMATIONS:
    - Purple glow: radial gradient expanding from center (800ms, easeOut)
    - Gold flash: electric gold (#FFD700) burst at peak (400ms, easeInOut)
    - Logo solidify: UNJYNX wordmark materializes from particles (300ms, easeIn)
    - Light mode variant: glow is soft lavender, flash is rich gold (#B8860B)
    - Haptic: single medium impact at gold flash moment

  ACCESSIBILITY:
    - reduceMotion: skip animation, show static logo for 1s, then route
    - Screen reader: "UNJYNX. Loading." announced once

  TESTS (target count):
    - Unit: 4 (auth state detection, first-launch flag, routing logic, offline fallback)
    - Widget: 3 (animation renders, logo appears, routes correctly per state)
    - Integration: 1 (full splash-to-route flow)


SCREEN B1: WELCOME CAROUSEL (Free — all tiers, 3 slides)
Phase: 1
─────────────────────────────────────────

  PURPOSE:
    First-time onboarding carousel. 3 slides introducing UNJYNX value props:
    1) Break the Forgetting Curse, 2) Reminders Where You Live,
    3) Your Day Your Way. Skip available on all slides. CTA → Personalization (B2).

  FRONTEND (Flutter):
    Package: feature_onboarding
    Route: /onboarding/welcome
    Key Widgets:
      - WelcomeCarousel — PageView with 3 slides, dot indicators at bottom
      - SlideOne — broken chain links → golden tasks animation (Rive/Lottie)
        Copy: "UNJYNX remembers so you don't have to."
      - SlideTwo — WhatsApp/Telegram/Instagram/SMS icons orbiting UNJYNX logo
        Copy: "Get reminders on WhatsApp, Telegram, Instagram, SMS."
      - SlideThree — Sunrise with Ghost Mode toggle, confetti burst
        Copy: "Ghost Mode when overwhelmed. Start now."
      - DotIndicator — 3 dots, active dot is gold, inactive is muted purple
      - SkipButton — top-right, muted text "Skip" → routes to B4 with defaults
      - NextButton — bottom, gold "Next" on slides 1-2, "Let's Unjynx!" on slide 3
    State Management:
      - carouselPageProvider (StateProvider<int>) — current slide index (0-2)
      - onboardingCompleteProvider — marks carousel as seen (SharedPreferences)
    Packages (pub.dev):
      - smooth_page_indicator ^1.2.0 — dot indicators
      - rive ^0.13.0 — slide animations (or lottie ^3.0.0)
    Drift Tables (local):
      - (none — uses SharedPreferences for onboarding state)

  BACKEND (Hono/TypeScript):
    Endpoints:
      (none — carousel is fully client-side)

    Business Logic:
      - No server interaction. Pure UI flow.
      - Skip sets default personalization (identity: "Professional", productivity:
        "Moderate", channels: push-only, daily content: "Motivation").

  DATA FLOW:
    B1 loads → user swipes through 3 slides → "Let's Unjynx!" tapped → route to
    B2 (personalization) → OR skip → set defaults in SharedPreferences → route
    to B4 (notification permission)

  INTERACTIONS & ANIMATIONS:
    - Page swipe: smooth physics-based scrolling (PageView default)
    - Dot transition: gold fill animates (200ms, easeInOut)
    - Slide 1 animation: chain links shatter → reform as golden task cards (1.2s loop)
    - Slide 2 animation: channel icons orbit in elliptical path (continuous, 4s period)
    - Slide 3 animation: sunrise gradient + Ghost Mode toggle demo + confetti burst
    - CTA button: gold with slight pulse animation when idle (2s period, subtle scale 1.0→1.02)
    - Skip: no animation, instant route

  ACCESSIBILITY:
    - Screen reader: each slide announces its copy text
    - Swipe alternative: Next/Skip buttons for users who can't swipe
    - reduceMotion: static illustrations instead of animated ones

  TESTS (target count):
    - Unit: 3 (page navigation, skip sets defaults, carousel completion flag)
    - Widget: 5 (3 slides render, dot indicator updates, skip/next buttons work)
    - Integration: 1 (full carousel → route to B2 or B4)


SCREEN D1: QUICK CREATE SHEET (Free — bottom sheet)
Phase: 1
─────────────────────────────────────────

  PURPOSE:
    Primary task creation entry point. Triggered by center "+" FAB from any screen.
    Bottom sheet with NLP-enabled text input, voice input, and quick-access icons
    for date, priority, project, tags, recurrence, attachments. Task drops into
    list with spring animation after creation.

  FRONTEND (Flutter):
    Package: feature_todos
    Route: (modal bottom sheet, no dedicated route — shown via showModalBottomSheet)
    Key Widgets:
      - QuickCreateSheet — DraggableScrollableSheet with text input at top
      - TaskTitleInput — TextField with NLP parsing hint ("Add a task...")
        NLP examples: "Buy groceries tomorrow at 5pm" → auto-sets date/time
      - VoiceInputButton — microphone icon, right of text field, speech-to-text
      - QuickActionRow — horizontal icon row below text field:
        - CalendarIcon → DateTimePicker (date + optional time)
        - FlagIcon → PrioritySelector (P1-P4, color-coded chips)
        - FolderIcon → ProjectSelector (searchable dropdown of user projects)
        - TagIcon → TagInput (autocomplete from existing tags)
        - RepeatIcon → RecurrenceBuilder (RRULE visual builder)
        - PaperclipIcon → AttachmentPicker (Pro only, shows upgrade prompt if Free)
      - CameraToTaskButton — (Pro) camera icon: whiteboard/screenshot → OCR → tasks
      - SubmitButton — "Add to [Project Name]" gold full-width button
      - TaskDropAnimation — spring animation: new task card drops into list below
    State Management:
      - quickCreateProvider (StateNotifier<QuickCreateState>) — form state
        Fields: title, dueDate, priority, projectId, tags, recurrence, attachments
      - nlpParserProvider — parses natural language for date/time/priority extraction
      - voiceInputProvider (AsyncNotifier) — speech-to-text state
    Packages (pub.dev):
      - speech_to_text ^7.0.0 — voice input
      - rrule ^0.2.0 — RRULE generation/parsing
    Drift Tables (local):
      - todos — insert new task row
      - projects — project list for selector
      - tags — tag list for autocomplete

  BACKEND (Hono/TypeScript):
    Endpoints:
      POST /api/v1/tasks
        Request: { title, description?, dueDate?, priority?, projectId?,
                   tags?: string[], recurrence?: string (RRULE), attachments?: FileRef[] }
        Response: { task: Task, syncId: string }
        Notes: Offline-first — task created locally in Drift first, synced when online.
               Server generates syncId for conflict resolution.

    Business Logic:
      - NLP parsing (v1): regex-based date/time extraction client-side
        Patterns: "tomorrow", "next Monday", "at 3pm", "every weekday"
      - NLP parsing (v2): Claude Haiku API for complex natural language
      - Voice: speech_to_text → text → same NLP pipeline
      - Attachments: uploaded to MinIO, reference stored in task
      - Recurrence: RRULE string stored, server generates future instances via BullMQ cron

  DATA FLOW:
    User taps "+" FAB → QuickCreateSheet appears (bottom sheet) → user types or speaks
    → NLP parser extracts date/priority if present → user optionally sets project/tags
    → "Add" tapped → Drift insert (local) → UI closes with spring animation →
    task appears in list → background sync to server when online

  INTERACTIONS & ANIMATIONS:
    - Sheet appear: slide up from bottom (300ms, Curves.easeOutCubic)
    - NLP detection: when date/time detected, chip auto-appears below text with
      parsed value (fadeIn 200ms). User can tap to edit or dismiss.
    - Priority selection: color fills flag icon (instant, with haptic light)
    - Submit: gold button → shrinks slightly (100ms) → expands back → sheet dismisses
    - Task drop: new task card slides into list position with spring physics
      (damping 0.7, stiffness 300)
    - Voice: microphone pulses red while recording (scale 1.0→1.1, 500ms loop)

  ACCESSIBILITY:
    - Voice input provides alternative to typing
    - All quick action icons have semantic labels
    - Screen reader: announces NLP-detected values ("Date set to tomorrow at 5 PM")
    - Keyboard: Tab cycles through quick actions

  TESTS (target count):
    - Unit: 8 (NLP parser: 4 date patterns, priority extraction, tag parsing,
      RRULE generation, task creation model)
    - Widget: 6 (sheet renders, all 6 quick action icons, submit flow, voice button,
      NLP chip display, attachment Pro gate)
    - Integration: 2 (full create-to-list flow, offline create + sync)


SCREEN D3: TASK LIST VIEW (Full — Free)
Phase: 1
─────────────────────────────────────────

  PURPOSE:
    Full task list with filters, sort, view toggle, bulk actions, and search.
    Accessed from Home "See all" or Project detail. Supports List/Kanban(Pro)/Compact
    views. Long-press activates multi-select for bulk operations.

  FRONTEND (Flutter):
    Package: feature_todos
    Route: /tasks (or /projects/:id/tasks when scoped to project)
    Key Widgets:
      - TaskListView — main scrollable list with SliverAppBar
      - FilterChipBar — horizontal scrollable chip row at top:
        Chips: All | Today | Upcoming | Overdue | No Date | Completed
        + PriorityFilter (P1-P4) + EnergyFilter (Low/Med/High/Peak)
        + TagFilter (multi-select) + AssigneeFilter (team mode)
      - SortSelector — dropdown: Due date | Priority | Created | Alphabetical | Energy
      - ViewToggle — segmented control top-right: List | Kanban (Pro) | Compact
      - TaskCard — individual task row: checkbox + title + due date + priority flag
        + project color dot + assignee avatar (team)
      - BulkActionBar — appears on long-press multi-select:
        Actions: Complete all | Move to project | Reschedule | Delete | Set priority
      - SearchBar — magnifying glass → full-text search with filter integration
      - EmptyState — illustration + "No tasks match your filters" or "All caught up!"
    State Management:
      - taskListProvider (AsyncNotifier) — filtered/sorted task list from Drift
      - activeFiltersProvider (StateNotifier<TaskFilters>) — current filter state
      - sortOrderProvider (StateProvider<SortOrder>) — current sort
      - viewModeProvider (StateProvider<ViewMode>) — list/kanban/compact
      - selectedTasksProvider (StateNotifier<Set<String>>) — multi-select state
      - searchQueryProvider (StateProvider<String>) — search text
    Packages (pub.dev):
      - (standard Flutter widgets — no special packages needed)
    Drift Tables (local):
      - todos — full task data with filter/sort queries
      - projects — for project filter
      - tags — for tag filter

  BACKEND (Hono/TypeScript):
    Endpoints:
      GET /api/v1/tasks
        Query: ?filter=today|upcoming|overdue|nodate|completed
               &priority=1,2,3,4 &energy=low,med,high,peak
               &tags=tag1,tag2 &projectId=xxx &assignee=userId
               &sort=dueDate|priority|created|alpha|energy &order=asc|desc
               &search=query &page=1 &limit=50
        Response: { tasks: Task[], total: number, page: number, hasMore: boolean }

      POST /api/v1/tasks/bulk
        Request: { taskIds: string[], action: "complete"|"move"|"reschedule"|"delete"|"priority",
                   payload?: { projectId?, dueDate?, priority? } }
        Response: { updated: number, tasks: Task[] }

    Business Logic:
      - Offline-first: all filtering/sorting done locally via Drift queries
      - Server queries only used for cross-device sync or team task lists
      - Bulk actions: atomic transaction, all-or-nothing
      - Search: local SQLite FTS5 full-text search (Drift), server uses PostgreSQL tsvector
      - Pagination: cursor-based for server, offset-based for local (small datasets)

  DATA FLOW:
    Screen loads → taskListProvider queries Drift with current filters/sort →
    renders TaskCard list → user taps filter chip → activeFiltersProvider updates →
    taskListProvider re-queries → list animates changes (AnimatedList) →
    long-press → selectedTasksProvider tracks selection → bulk action bar appears →
    action applied to all selected → Drift updates → sync to server

  INTERACTIONS & ANIMATIONS:
    - Filter chip select: gold fill + slight scale bounce (150ms)
    - Task complete: checkbox fills gold → task slides right and fades out (400ms)
    - Bulk select: long-press vibrates (haptic heavy) → cards show checkmarks
    - Pull-to-refresh: custom refresh indicator with UNJYNX brand animation
    - View toggle: crossfade between List/Kanban/Compact (300ms)
    - Search: expands from icon to full-width input (250ms, easeOutCubic)
    - Empty state: illustration has subtle breathing animation (2s loop)

  ACCESSIBILITY:
    - Bulk actions accessible via long-press OR menu button (for switch users)
    - Filter chips announce active state ("Today filter: active")
    - Task cards announce: title, priority, due date, completion status

  TESTS (target count):
    - Unit: 8 (all filter types, sort orders, search query, bulk action logic,
      pagination, empty state detection)
    - Widget: 8 (filter bar renders, sort works, view toggle, task cards,
      bulk select, search, empty state, pull-to-refresh)
    - Integration: 2 (filter+sort combo, bulk action + sync)


SCREEN E2: PROJECT DETAIL SCREEN (Free — full screen)
Phase: 2
─────────────────────────────────────────

  PURPOSE:
    Full project view. Shows project metadata (name, description, color, icon,
    members), progress ring, task list scoped to project with view toggle
    (List/Kanban/Timeline-Team), sections for task grouping, drag between sections.
    Team features: activity feed, member management, visibility settings.

  FRONTEND (Flutter):
    Package: feature_projects
    Route: /projects/:id
    Key Widgets:
      - ProjectHeader — project name (editable inline) + color/icon + description
      - ProgressRing — circular progress indicator: completed/total tasks (%)
      - MemberAvatarRow — horizontal avatar list with roles (team mode)
      - ProjectTaskList — TaskListView scoped to this project (reuses D3 components)
      - ViewToggle — List | Kanban (Pro) | Timeline/Gantt (Team plan)
      - SectionList — user-created sections to group tasks within project
        - SectionHeader — section name + task count + collapse toggle
        - DragTarget — drag tasks between sections (ReorderableListView)
      - AddSectionButton — "Add section" at bottom of section list
      - ProjectActivityFeed — (Team) who did what, when (scrollable timeline)
      - MemberManagement — (Team) invite by email/username, assign roles, remove
      - ProjectSettingsButton — visibility (Personal/Team/Public), archive, delete
    State Management:
      - projectDetailProvider (AsyncNotifier<Project>) — project metadata
      - projectTasksProvider (AsyncNotifier) — tasks filtered to this project
      - sectionsProvider (AsyncNotifier<List<Section>>) — project sections
      - projectMembersProvider (AsyncNotifier) — team members (Team plan)
      - projectActivityProvider (AsyncNotifier) — activity feed (Team plan)
    Packages (pub.dev):
      - (standard Flutter widgets — uses same components as D3)
    Drift Tables (local):
      - projects — project metadata
      - todos — tasks filtered by projectId
      - sections — project sections with order
      - project_members — (Team) member-project associations

  BACKEND (Hono/TypeScript):
    Endpoints:
      GET /api/v1/projects/:id
        Response: { project: Project, memberCount: number, taskCount: number,
                    completedCount: number }

      PUT /api/v1/projects/:id
        Request: { name?, description?, color?, icon?, visibility?, isArchived? }
        Response: { project: Project }

      GET /api/v1/projects/:id/sections
        Response: { sections: Section[] }

      POST /api/v1/projects/:id/sections
        Request: { name: string, order: number }
        Response: { section: Section }

      PUT /api/v1/projects/:id/sections/:sectionId
        Request: { name?, order? }
        Response: { section: Section }

      DELETE /api/v1/projects/:id/sections/:sectionId
        Notes: Moves orphaned tasks to "No Section" default

      GET /api/v1/projects/:id/activity (Team plan)
        Query: ?page=1&limit=20
        Response: { activities: Activity[], hasMore: boolean }

      POST /api/v1/projects/:id/members (Team plan)
        Request: { email: string, role: "viewer"|"editor"|"admin" }
        Response: { member: ProjectMember }

      DELETE /api/v1/projects/:id/members/:memberId (Team plan)

    Business Logic:
      - Sections: ordered list, drag-to-reorder sends PUT with new order values
      - Progress: calculated from tasks where projectId matches
      - Visibility: Personal (only creator), Team (workspace members), Public (shareable link)
      - Archive: soft-delete, tasks remain but hidden from active views
      - Activity feed: event-sourced log of all project changes (Team plan)

  DATA FLOW:
    Route /projects/:id → projectDetailProvider loads project + tasks + sections →
    user edits name inline → PUT /projects/:id → Drift update → header refreshes →
    user drags task between sections → section assignment updated → Drift + API sync

  INTERACTIONS & ANIMATIONS:
    - Progress ring: fills with spring animation on load (600ms)
    - Inline edit: tap name → text becomes editable with underline, save on unfocus
    - Section collapse: smooth height animation (200ms, easeInOut)
    - Drag between sections: card lifts with shadow elevation + haptic medium
    - Member avatar: tap → role popup (viewer/editor/admin selector)
    - Archive: slide left on project header → confirm dialog → fade out

  ACCESSIBILITY:
    - Sections collapsible via tap or keyboard
    - Drag alternative: "Move to section" in task context menu
    - Progress ring announces percentage ("Project 65% complete")

  TESTS (target count):
    - Unit: 6 (progress calculation, section ordering, visibility rules,
      member role permissions, archive logic, activity logging)
    - Widget: 6 (header renders, progress ring, section list, drag-to-reorder,
      member avatars, inline edit)
    - Integration: 2 (full project CRUD, section drag + task reassignment)


SCREEN F3: POMODORO TIMER SCREEN (Free — all tiers)
Phase: 2
─────────────────────────────────────────

  PURPOSE:
    Full-screen focus mode. Large circular timer (25 min work / 5 min break,
    configurable). Current task displayed. Session counter. Ambient sounds.
    Minimizes to floating bubble when navigating away. Post-session feedback
    + auto-log time to task. Game Mode XP integration (if enabled).

  FRONTEND (Flutter):
    Package: feature_todos (or feature_focus)
    Route: /focus/pomodoro (or modal overlay)
    Key Widgets:
      - PomodoroTimer — large circular countdown timer (CustomPainter arc)
        - Work: 25 min default (configurable 15/20/25/30/45/60)
        - Break: 5 min short, 15 min long (every 4th session)
      - CurrentTaskCard — displays the task being focused on (title + priority)
      - SessionCounter — "Pomodoro 3 of 4" text with dot indicators
      - TimerControls — Start (gold) | Pause (outline) | Reset (muted)
      - AmbientSoundSelector — horizontal scrollable:
        Rain | Forest | Cafe | Lo-fi | Ocean | Silence (each with icon)
      - FloatingBubble — overlay widget when user navigates away:
        Small circle showing remaining time, tappable to return
      - PostSessionSheet — bottom sheet after completion:
        - "How focused were you?" slider (1-5 stars)
        - Time auto-logged to task
        - Focus ring fill + completion feedback
        - XP earned (only if Game Mode on, e.g., "+15 XP")
    State Management:
      - pomodoroProvider (StateNotifier<PomodoroState>) — timer state machine
        States: idle → running → paused → breakTime → completed
        Fields: currentSeconds, totalSeconds, sessionsCompleted, isBreak
      - ambientSoundProvider (StateProvider<AmbientSound>) — selected sound
      - focusTaskProvider (StateProvider<Task?>) — task being focused on
      - focusHistoryProvider (AsyncNotifier) — logs completed Pomodoro sessions
    Packages (pub.dev):
      - audioplayers ^6.0.0 — ambient sound playback (local assets)
      - flutter_overlay_window ^0.4.0 — floating bubble (Android)
        (iOS: PiP not available for non-video, use local notification instead)
    Drift Tables (local):
      - focus_sessions — log: taskId, duration, rating, completedAt
      - todos — update timeSpent field after session

  BACKEND (Hono/TypeScript):
    Endpoints:
      POST /api/v1/focus/sessions
        Request: { taskId: string, duration: number, rating: 1-5,
                   sessionsCompleted: number, type: "pomodoro"|"freeform" }
        Response: { session: FocusSession, xpEarned?: number }
        Notes: XP calculated server-side if Game Mode enabled

      GET /api/v1/focus/stats
        Query: ?range=7d|30d|90d
        Response: { totalMinutes: number, avgRating: number,
                    sessionsCount: number, byDay: DailyFocusStats[] }

    Business Logic:
      - Timer runs client-side (no server pinging during focus)
      - Session logged to server only on completion (not on pause/abandon)
      - Abandoned sessions (< 50% completed) not logged (prevent gaming)
      - XP: 10 XP per completed Pomodoro + 5 bonus for 5-star focus rating
      - Ambient sounds: bundled assets (no streaming), ~2MB total
      - Floating bubble: Android overlay permission required (prompted once)

  DATA FLOW:
    User selects task → opens Pomodoro → taps Start → timer counts down →
    pomodoroProvider ticks every second → on complete: haptic + sound →
    PostSessionSheet appears → user rates focus → POST /focus/sessions →
    Drift insert focus_sessions + update todo.timeSpent → return to task list

  INTERACTIONS & ANIMATIONS:
    - Timer arc: smooth countdown, arc shrinks (CustomPainter repaint every 1s)
    - Start: gold button pulses once then stays solid
    - Complete: timer ring fills gold → burst particles → haptic heavy + chime sound
    - Break transition: work ring fades → break ring appears (green) (500ms crossfade)
    - Session dots: fill gold sequentially as sessions complete
    - Ambient sound: fade in over 2s when selected, crossfade when switching
    - Floating bubble: subtle pulse animation (scale 1.0→1.05, 2s loop)
    - Focus rating: stars fill with staggered animation (100ms per star)

  ACCESSIBILITY:
    - Timer announces remaining time every 5 minutes (screen reader)
    - Controls have large tap targets (min 48x48)
    - Ambient sounds have visual equalizer indicator for deaf users
    - Haptic feedback on complete (important for visually impaired)

  TESTS (target count):
    - Unit: 6 (timer countdown, session tracking, break logic, XP calculation,
      abandoned session rejection, time logging to task)
    - Widget: 6 (timer renders, controls work, ambient selector, session counter,
      post-session sheet, floating bubble)
    - Integration: 2 (full pomodoro cycle, focus stats accumulation)


SCREEN J1: CHANNEL HUB SCREEN (Free — settings)
Phase: 3
─────────────────────────────────────────

  PURPOSE:
    Central management for all notification channels. Shows connection status
    for: Push, Telegram (Free), Email (Free), WhatsApp (Pro), SMS (Pro),
    Instagram (Pro), Slack (Pro), Discord (Pro). Each channel expandable to
    show details, test message, quiet hours, digest mode, fallback order.

  FRONTEND (Flutter):
    Package: feature_channels
    Route: /settings/channels (or /channels)
    Key Widgets:
      - ChannelHubList — ListView of ChannelCard widgets (one per channel)
      - ChannelCard — expandable card per channel:
        - Icon + name + connection status badge (green/gray/red)
        - Tier badge (Free/Pro) — Pro channels show lock icon if user is Free
        - Expanded view:
          - ConnectionStatus — "Connected since [date]" or "Not connected"
          - LastMessageInfo — "Last reminder sent: [time]"
          - TestMessageButton — "Send me a test reminder" → sends via API
          - QuietHoursToggle — per-channel override (start/end time pickers)
          - DigestModeToggle — batch notifications for this channel
          - FallbackOrderInfo — "If this fails, try: [next channel]"
          - DisconnectButton — red, with confirmation dialog
      - ConnectButton — per channel: routes to J2/J3/J4/J6 connection flows
      - UpgradePrompt — shown inline for Pro channels when user is Free:
        "Unlock WhatsApp reminders with Pro" + upgrade CTA
    State Management:
      - channelListProvider (AsyncNotifier<List<Channel>>) — all channels + status
      - channelStatusProvider (family, per channel) — real-time connection status
      - testMessageProvider (AsyncNotifier) — send test message state
    Packages (pub.dev):
      - (standard Flutter widgets)
    Drift Tables (local):
      - notification_channels — channel type, status, config, lastMessageAt

  BACKEND (Hono/TypeScript):
    Endpoints:
      GET /api/v1/channels
        Response: { channels: Channel[] }
        Channel: { type, status: "connected"|"disconnected"|"error",
                   connectedAt?, lastMessageAt?, config: ChannelConfig }

      POST /api/v1/channels/:type/test
        Response: { sent: boolean, messageId?: string, error?: string }
        Notes: Sends a test reminder via the specified channel

      DELETE /api/v1/channels/:type
        Response: { disconnected: true }
        Notes: Revokes tokens/unsubscribes. Consent records retained for compliance.

    Business Logic:
      - Channel status checked in real-time via WebSocket events
      - Test message: sends "This is a test from UNJYNX!" with task-like formatting
      - Disconnect: per channel — Telegram: deactivate bot, WhatsApp: opt-out,
        Instagram: unfollow, SMS: STOP, Slack/Discord: revoke OAuth
      - Free users see all channels but Pro ones show upgrade CTA
      - Fallback chain managed in J5 (notification preferences)

  DATA FLOW:
    ChannelHub loads → channelListProvider fetches channels from Drift (local) +
    API sync → renders ChannelCard list → user taps "Connect" → routes to J2/J3/J4/J6 →
    on return: channel status updated via WebSocket → card refreshes →
    user taps "Test" → testMessageProvider sends test → success/error shown

  INTERACTIONS & ANIMATIONS:
