    Uses Claude Haiku 4.5 (80%), Sonnet 4.6 (15%), Opus 4.6 (5%).

  FRONTEND (Flutter):
    Package: feature_ai (new package, v2)
    Route: /ai/chat
    Key Widgets:
      - AiChatView — chat-style interface with conversation bubbles
      - UserBubble — user message (right-aligned, purple surface)
      - AiBubble — AI response (left-aligned, surface container, gold accent)
        Supports: text, task cards (tappable), chart summaries, action buttons
      - VoiceInputButton — speak-to-AI (speech-to-text → AI → text-to-speech)
      - QuickActionChips — pre-built chips at bottom:
        "Suggest next task" | "Break this down" | "Schedule my day" | "Weekly report"
      - PersonaSelector — dropdown: Default | Drill Sergeant | Therapist | CEO | Coach
      - QuotaIndicator — (Free) "3 of 5 AI interactions remaining this month"
      - TaskActionCard — inline task card with [Create] [Schedule] [Add subtasks] buttons
    State Management:
      - aiChatProvider (AsyncNotifier<List<ChatMessage>>) — conversation history
      - aiPersonaProvider (StateProvider<AiPersona>) — selected persona
      - aiQuotaProvider (AsyncNotifier<AiQuota>) — remaining interactions
      - aiStreamProvider — streams AI response tokens for typing effect
    Packages (pub.dev):
      - flutter_chat_ui ^1.6.0 — chat interface (or custom)
      - speech_to_text ^7.0.0 — voice input
      - flutter_tts ^4.0.0 — text-to-speech for AI responses
    Drift Tables (local):
      - ai_conversations — conversation history (cached locally)

  BACKEND (Hono/TypeScript):
    Endpoints:
      POST /api/v1/ai/chat
        Request: { message: string, persona?: string, context?: TaskContext }
        Response (streaming): SSE stream of AI response tokens
        Notes: Routes to Claude API: Haiku for simple queries, Sonnet for complex,
               Opus for deep analysis. Persona modifies system prompt.

      GET /api/v1/ai/quota
        Response: { used: number, limit: number, resetsAt: string }

      POST /api/v1/ai/actions
        Request: { action: "create_task"|"schedule"|"decompose", payload: object }
        Response: { result: Task | Task[] | Schedule }
        Notes: Executes AI-suggested actions (user confirms first)

    Business Logic:
      - Model routing: keyword/complexity analysis determines Claude model tier
      - Persona: modifies system prompt (Drill Sergeant = tough love, Therapist = empathetic, etc.)
      - Context: AI has access to user's tasks, projects, completion history, energy levels
      - Task creation: AI can suggest tasks → user confirms → creates via standard task API
      - Decomposition: "Break down [task]" → AI generates subtask tree
      - Rate limiting: Free 5/mo, Pro unlimited (but 100/day server-side limit for abuse)
      - Cost management: Haiku for 80% of queries ($0.001/query avg)

  DATA FLOW:
    User taps AI button → AiChatView opens → user types or speaks → POST /ai/chat →
    SSE stream → AI response renders token-by-token → if AI suggests task creation:
    TaskActionCard shown → user taps [Create] → POST /ai/actions → task created →
    confirmation in chat

  INTERACTIONS & ANIMATIONS:
    - AI button: floating gold circle with sparkle icon, slight bounce on idle
    - Typing indicator: 3 dots pulsing while AI generates response
    - Token streaming: text appears character-by-character (typewriter effect, 30ms/char)
    - Task card: slides in from left with spring animation
    - Persona switch: avatar morphs between personas (crossfade 300ms)
    - Voice: microphone pulses while recording, speaker icon while TTS plays

  ACCESSIBILITY:
    - Voice input/output provides hands-free alternative
    - Chat history navigable by message (screen reader)
    - Quick action chips have descriptive labels
    - AI responses have "AI says:" prefix for screen reader clarity

  TESTS (target count):
    - Unit: 6 (model routing, persona prompt, quota tracking, action execution,
      context building, streaming parser)
    - Widget: 5 (chat renders, bubbles, quick chips, persona selector, quota indicator)
    - Integration: 2 (full chat flow with mock AI, action execution)


SCREEN K2: AI AUTO-SCHEDULE SCREEN (Pro — v2 deferred)
Phase: v2
─────────────────────────────────────────

  PURPOSE:
    (v2 — deferred) AI suggests optimal time slots for unscheduled tasks based
    on priority, deadlines, calendar conflicts, duration estimates, and
    productivity patterns. Preview in calendar view, drag to adjust, accept all
    or individual placements. Full undo support.

  FRONTEND (Flutter):
    Package: feature_ai (v2)
    Route: /ai/schedule
    Key Widgets:
      - UnscheduledTaskList — sidebar: tasks without scheduled time slots
      - SchedulePreview — calendar day/week view with AI-placed task blocks
        AI-suggested blocks: dashed gold border (not yet confirmed)
        Confirmed blocks: solid fill (standard task block style)
      - SuggestionCard — per task: AI explanation ("Placed at 10am because you're
        most productive in the morning and it aligns with your energy peak")
      - AcceptAllButton — gold CTA: accept entire AI schedule
      - UndoButton — revert all AI placements to original state
      - ConflictIndicator — red highlight if AI placement overlaps calendar event
      - DragHandle — drag AI-placed blocks to adjust time (snap to 15min increments)
    State Management:
      - autoScheduleProvider (AsyncNotifier<ScheduleSuggestion>) — AI schedule result
      - pendingSuggestionsProvider — list of unconfirmed AI placements
      - scheduleConflictsProvider — detected conflicts with existing events
    Packages (pub.dev):
      - (reuses calendar components from F1)
    Drift Tables (local):
      - schedule_suggestions — cached AI suggestions
      - todos — update scheduledAt after acceptance

  BACKEND (Hono/TypeScript):
    Endpoints:
      POST /api/v1/ai/schedule/suggest
        Request: { taskIds?: string[], dateRange: { start, end } }
        Response: { suggestions: ScheduleSuggestion[] }
        ScheduleSuggestion: { taskId, suggestedStart, suggestedEnd, reason,
                              confidence: 0-1, conflicts: CalendarEvent[] }
        Notes: Uses Claude Sonnet for scheduling logic. Considers:
               - Task priority + deadline urgency
               - Calendar events (Google Calendar sync)
               - Historical productivity patterns (by hour/day)
               - Energy level predictions
               - Duration estimates (learned from past similar tasks)

      POST /api/v1/ai/schedule/accept
        Request: { acceptedSuggestions: { taskId, start, end }[] }
        Response: { scheduled: number, tasks: Task[] }

      POST /api/v1/ai/schedule/undo
        Response: { reverted: number }
        Notes: Restores previous scheduledAt values from snapshot

    Business Logic:
      - Scheduling algorithm: constraint satisfaction + user preference learning
      - Conflict detection: checks Google Calendar + existing task blocks
      - Duration estimation: moving average of actual time for similar tasks
      - Confidence score: higher if more data available, lower for new task types
      - Undo: stores pre-schedule snapshot, full revert possible within 24h
      - Cost: ~$0.01 per schedule request (Sonnet, medium context)

  DATA FLOW:
    User opens K2 → POST /ai/schedule/suggest → AI analyzes tasks + calendar +
    patterns → returns suggestions → SchedulePreview renders with dashed blocks →
    user reviews/drags to adjust → taps "Accept All" or individual accept →
    POST /ai/schedule/accept → todos updated with scheduledAt → calendar view reflects

  INTERACTIONS & ANIMATIONS:
    - AI thinking: calendar shimmers with gold particles while generating
    - Suggestions appear: task blocks slide into calendar slots (staggered, 100ms each)
    - Dashed border: animated dash pattern (marching ants, 2s cycle)
    - Accept: dashed border solidifies (300ms transition)
    - Conflict: red pulse on overlapping area
    - Undo: all blocks slide back to unscheduled sidebar (reverse animation)

  TESTS (target count):
    - Unit: 5 (suggestion generation, conflict detection, duration estimation,
      acceptance flow, undo/snapshot)
    - Widget: 4 (preview renders, drag adjustment, accept/undo buttons, conflict indicator)
    - Integration: 2 (full suggest-accept flow, undo flow)


SCREEN K3: AI INSIGHTS SCREEN (Pro — v2 deferred)
Phase: v2
─────────────────────────────────────────

  PURPOSE:
    (v2 — deferred) Weekly auto-generated AI productivity report. Summary stats,
    pattern detection, actionable suggestions, week-over-week comparisons,
    predictions, and warnings about deferred tasks. Generated every Sunday
    evening via BullMQ cron job. Uses Claude Sonnet for analysis.

  FRONTEND (Flutter):
    Package: feature_ai (v2)
    Route: /ai/insights
    Key Widgets:
      - InsightsSummary — hero card: "You completed 34 of 41 tasks (83%)"
        with animated progress ring
      - PatternsSection — "Your most productive day is Wednesday"
        Visual: bar chart highlighting peak day
      - SuggestionsSection — actionable cards:
        "Consider scheduling creative tasks before 11 AM"
        Each card has [Apply] button to act on suggestion
      - ComparisonSection — "12% more productive than last week"
        Visual: line chart comparing current vs previous week
      - PredictionsSection — "At current pace, you'll finish Project X by March 20"
        Visual: timeline with projected completion dates
      - WarningsSection — amber cards:
        "3 tasks deferred more than 3 times — consider removing or delegating"
        Each warning has [View Tasks] button
      - WeekSelector — navigate between past weekly reports
    State Management:
      - weeklyInsightsProvider (AsyncNotifier<WeeklyInsight>) — current week's report
      - insightHistoryProvider (AsyncNotifier) — past reports for comparison
      - selectedWeekProvider (StateProvider<DateTime>) — which week to view
    Packages (pub.dev):
      - fl_chart ^0.70.0 — charts for patterns, comparisons
    Drift Tables (local):
      - weekly_insights — cached weekly reports

  BACKEND (Hono/TypeScript):
    Endpoints:
      GET /api/v1/ai/insights/weekly
        Query: ?week=2026-03-09 (ISO date, start of week)
        Response: { insight: WeeklyInsight }
        WeeklyInsight: {
          summary: { completed, total, rate, streakDays },
          patterns: Pattern[],
          suggestions: Suggestion[],
          comparison: { vsPrevWeek: number, vsPrevMonth: number },
          predictions: Prediction[],
          warnings: Warning[]
        }

      POST /api/v1/ai/insights/generate (internal, BullMQ trigger)
        Notes: Generates weekly insight for all Pro users. Runs Sunday 8pm user timezone.
               Uses Claude Sonnet to analyze task data and generate natural language insights.

    Business Logic:
      - BullMQ cron: every Sunday 8pm per user timezone → gathers week's task data
      - Claude Sonnet: generates natural language insights from structured data
      - Pattern detection: aggregates by day-of-week, hour-of-day, project, tag
      - Predictions: linear regression on completion rates per project
      - Warnings: flags tasks deferred 3+ times, overdue 7+ days, projects stalled
      - Suggestions: based on patterns (e.g., "you complete 40% more tasks on Wednesdays")
      - Cost: ~$0.005 per weekly report (Sonnet, medium context)
      - Caching: generated once, served from cache until next week

  DATA FLOW:
    Sunday 8pm → BullMQ job triggers → aggregates user's week data → POST to Claude
    Sonnet → parses AI response → stores WeeklyInsight → push notification: "Your
    weekly report is ready" → user opens K3 → weeklyInsightsProvider loads from
    API/cache → renders all sections

  INTERACTIONS & ANIMATIONS:
    - Summary ring: fills with spring animation on load (800ms)
    - Pattern chart bars: staggered grow animation (100ms delay per bar)
    - Suggestion cards: slide in from right (staggered, 150ms each)
    - Comparison line chart: draws left-to-right (1s, easeInOut)
    - Warning cards: subtle amber pulse border (3s period)
    - Week navigation: horizontal swipe with crossfade (300ms)

  ACCESSIBILITY:
    - All charts have text alternatives read by screen reader
    - Suggestions are actionable: screen reader announces action button
    - Comparison announced as text: "12 percent more productive than last week"

  TESTS (target count):
    - Unit: 5 (report generation, pattern detection, prediction algorithm,
      warning thresholds, comparison calculation)
    - Widget: 5 (summary card, patterns section, suggestions, comparisons, warnings)
    - Integration: 2 (full report generation + display, week navigation)


